memory leak when input ends in ' '
fixed with an or statement at the end of input function for checking if word_l == 0

test cases

gcc -o sfrob -g sfrob.c

valgrind --leak-check=full ./sfrob

printf '*~BO *{_CIA *hXE]D *LER #@_GZY #E\\OX #^BO #FKPS #NEM\4 ' | valgrind --leak-check=full ./sfrob | od -ta
